review_blob: This was a beer I was excited to try. So maybe this brew ISNT as good as I think it is. But it is fantastic. Nice refined carbonation. Is it bottle-conditioned?

Hard to believe Ipswich is kinda off the radar. Theyve been making some of the Easts best beer for decades now. This one is special, a seasonal with local hops and above all local malting by the incredible Valley Malt. A very distinctive hoppy brew. One of my all-time favorites.
beer_name: Ipswich Five Mile Hop Harvest IPA

review_blob: A very refined single-hop (citra) ale. Got a growler from the brewery the day it was harvested. This is a brewery to watch. Only 4.1 abv so a fine session brew. Excellent low alcohol ale.
